      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You absolutely need to avoid alcohol while taking metronidazole, no exceptions! Mixing it with wine can cause a severe reaction called disulfiram-like reaction, leading to nausea, vomiting, and a pounding headache. To be safe and follow the best medical advice, you should wait until you have completely finished your entire week-long course of the medication before having even a sip of wine. Stick to the plan and let the medicine do its job without any interference!",
